Description: Rim sherd of Chian pottery oenochoe; white slip; exterior: brown line on edge of rim, reserved below with painted inscription.
Curator's comments: The number '922' is written in pencil on the interior surface of the sherd. For parallels, see Boardman, J., Excavations in Chios 1952-1955. Greek Emporio. Annual of the British School at Athens Supplement 6. Oxford 1967, 144-5.
Bibliographic references: Cook & Woodhead 1952 / Painted Inscriptions on Chiot Pottery (p. 166, no. 51)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 719, no. 774)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.0062) (phase 2)
